st%20few%20days.%20While%20the%20maximum%20temperature%20has%20been%20hovering%20around%20the%2050%20degrees%20Celsius%20mark%2C%20the%20minimum%20is%20inching%20closer%20to%20the%2030%20degrees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20weather%20office%20had%20earlier%20warned%20of%20extreme%20heat%20in%20most%20parts%20of%20the%20national%20capital.%20The%20India%20Meteorological%20Department%20forecast%20for%20today%20predicted%20a%20maximum%20temperature%20of%2045.8%20degrees.%20However%2C%20at%202.30%20pm%20today%2C%20the%20weather%20station%20in%20Delhi's%20Mungeshpur%20recorded%20a%20temperature%20of%2052.3%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%20the%20highest-ever%20in%20any%20part%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20IMD%20regional%20head%20Kuldeep%20Srivastava%2C%20areas%20such%20as%20Mungeshpur%20and%20Narela%20on%20Delhi's%20outskirts%20are%20the%20first%20to%20receive%20hot%20winds%20coming%20in%20from%20Rajasthan%2C%20leading%20to%20extreme%20heat%20conditions.%20%26quot%3BParts%20of%20Delhi%20are%20particularly%20susceptible%20to%20the%20early%20arrival%20of%20these%20hot%20winds%2C%20worsening%20the%20already%20severe%20weather.%20Areas%20like%20Mungeshpur%2C%20Narela%20and%20Najafgarh%20are%20the%20first%20to%20experience%20the%20full%20force%20of%20these%20hot%20winds%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20according%20to%20a%20PTI%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMahesh%20Palawat%2C%20vice%20president%20of%20Meteorology%20and%20Climate%20Change%20at%20Skymet%20Weather%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIn%20open%20areas%20with%20vacant%20land%2C%20there%20is%20increased%20radiation.%20Direct%20sunlight%20and%20lack%20of%20shade%20make%20these%20regions%20exceptionally%20hot.%20When%20wind%20blows%20from%20the%20west%2C%20it%20affects%20these%20areas%20first.%20As%20they%20are%20on%20the%20outskirts%2C%20temperatures%20rise%20rapidly%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Palawat%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20national%20capital%20sizzles%20and%20air-conditioners%20run%20overtime%2C%20power%20demand%20has%20gone%20up.%20Power%20demand%20in%20Delhi%20touched%20an%20all-time%20high%20of%208%2C302%20MW%20today%2C%20officials%20have%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20officials%20said%20this%20is%20the%20first%20time%20in%20the%20history%20of%20the%20national%20capital%20that%20power%20demand%20has%20crossed%20the%208%2C300-MW%20mark%20--%20100%20MW%20more%20than%20what%20power%20distribution%20companies%20had%20predicted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20add%20to%20Delhiites'%20problems%2C%20a%20water%20crisis%20is%20on%20the%20horizon.%20Delhi%20minister%20Atishi%20has%20said%20the%20Haryana%20government%20is%20not%20giving%20the%20national%20capital%20its%20share%20of%20Yamuna%20water%20and%20this%20has%20led%20to%20water%20crisis%20in%20some%20areas.%20The%20AAP%20government%20today%20directed%20Delhi%20Jal%20Board%20to%20form%20200%20teams%20to%20monitor%20and%20minimise%20water%20wastage.%20Washing%20cars%20with%20hose%20pipes%2C%20overflowing%20tanks%20and%20use%20of%20drinking%20water%20for%20commercial%20purposes%20will%20now%20attract%20a%20fine%20of%20Rs%202%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716985440000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-03%2Fm8fadvio_delhi-rain_625x300_24_March_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Frain-in-delhi-after-temperature-hits-record-high-of-52-3-degrees-5771677%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Two%20hours%20after%20Delhi%20recorded%20the%20country's%20highest-ever%20temperature%20at%2052.3%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%20the%20national%20capital%20received%20showers%20this%20afternoon%2C%20bringing%20much-needed%20respite%20from%20extreme%20heat.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Frain-in-delhi-after-temperature-hits-record-high-of-52-3-degrees-5771677%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Frain-in-delhi-after-temperature-hits-record-