3Cp%3EIf%20you%20are%20in%20Delhi-NCR%20and%20it%20felt%20like%20your%20skin%20was%20sizzling%20this%20afternoon%20or%20you%20thought%20it%20was%20the%20hottest%20it%20has%20ever%20been%2C%20you%20were%20not%20wrong.%20The%20national%20capital%20recorded%20its%20highest-ever%20temperature%20of%2052.3%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%20just%204.4%20degrees%20shy%20of%20the%20highest%20temperature%20ever%20recorded%20on%20Earth%3A%2056.7%20degrees%20Celsius%20at%20the%20Greenland%20Ranch%20in%20California's%20Death%20Valley.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ranch%20is%20now%20aptly%20called%20the%20Furnace%20Creek%20Ranch.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20data%20from%20the%20India%20Meteorological%20Department%2C%20the%20Mungeshpur%20weather%20station%20in%20northwest%20Delhi%20recorded%20the%20temperature-bulb-shattering%20number%20at%202.30%20pm.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIMD%20regional%20head%20Kuldeep%20Srivastava%20said%20the%20city's%20outskirts%20are%20the%20first%20areas%20to%20be%20hit%20by%20hot%20winds%20from%20Rajasthan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BParts%20of%20Delhi%20are%20particularly%20susceptible%20to%20the%20early%20arrival%20of%20these%20hot%20winds%2C%20worsening%20the%20already%20severe%20weather.%20Areas%20like%20Mungeshpur%2C%20Narela%20and%20Najafgarh%20are%20the%20first%20to%20experience%20the%20full%20force%20of%20these%20hot%20winds%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20was%20quoted%20as%20saying%20by%20news%20agency%20PTI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%2051%20degrees%20Celsius%2C%20the%20previous%20highest%20temperature%20in%20India%20was%20recorded%20in%20Rajasthan's%20Phalodi%20in%202016.%20This%20was%20followed%20by%2050.8%20degrees%20in%20Churu%2C%20also%20in%20the%20desert%20state%2C%20in%202019%20and%2050.6%20degrees%20in%20Alwar%20in%201956.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20world's%20highest%20temperature%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Guinness%20World%20Records%2C%20was%20recorded%20on%20July%2010%2C%201913.%20There%20is%20some%20dispute%20about%20the%20number%2C%20though%2C%20and%20if%20the%20current%20record%20is%20decertified%20-%20%C2%A0like%20the%20figure%20of%2057.8%20degrees%20Celsius%20recorded%20in%20Libya%20in%201922%20-%20then%20the%20next%20highest%20figure%20will%20be%2054%20degrees%2C%20just%201.7%20degrees%20higher%20than%20Delhi's%20temperature%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20national%20capital%20also%20recorded%20its%20all-time%20high%20power%20demand%20of%208%2C302%20megawatts%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20powered%20by%20increased%20use%20of%20air%20conditioners.%20The%20use%20of%20air%20conditioners%2C%20however%2C%20also%20adds%20to%20the%20temperature%20by%20exacerbating%20the%20heat%20island%20effect%20in%20urban%20areas.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20NDTV%20earlier%2C%20Robert%20Muir-Wood%2C%20Chief%20Research%20Officer%20at%20Moody's%20RMS%2C%20had%20said%20temperatures%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20cities%20can%20be%20as%20many%20as%20seven%20degrees%20higher%20than%20the%20areas%20surrounding%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EListing%20the%20main%20causes%20of%20the%20heat%20island%20effect%2C%20Mr%20Muir-Wood%20had%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20three%20drivers%2C%20the%20first%20reason%20is%20that%20the%20surfaces%20of%20the%20buildings%2C%20the%20surfaces%20of%20the%20roads%20absorb%20a%20lot%20of%20heat.%20They%20tend%20to%20be%20dark%20materials.%20They%20may%20be%20glass%20and%20concrete%2C%20but%20they%20absorb%20a%20lot%20of%20heat.%20The%20second%20reason%20is%20that%20there%20are%20lower%20wind%20speeds%20inside%20a%20metropolitan%20area%20where%20you%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20big%20buildings.%20The%20bigger%20the%20buildings%2C%20the%20more%20they%20are%20slowing%20down%20the%20wind.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20third%20factor%20is%20that%20there%20will%20be%20a%20lot%20of%20air%20conditioning%20plants%20and%20other%20machinery%2C%20and%20cars%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20city%2C%20and%20they%20are%20all%20producing%20heat%20too.%20Depending%20on%20how%20concentrated%20the%20population%20of%20buildings%20is%2C%20it%20can%20drive%20up%20the%20temperatures%20by%20five%2C%20six%20or%20seven%20degrees%20centigrade%20in%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20city%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20expert%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716983040000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Fra3q26oo_heatwave-ians_625x300_06_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdelhi-temperature-now-just-4-4-degrees-shy-of-world-record-set-in-1913-5771883%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20you%20are%20in%20Delhi-NCR%20and%20it%20felt%20like%20your%20skin%20was%20sizzling%20this%20afternoon%20or%20you%20thought%20it%20was%20the%20hottest%20it%20has%20ever%20been%2C%20you%20were%20not%20wrong.%20The%20national%20capital%20recorded%20its%20highest-ever%20temperature%20of%2052.3%20degrees%20Celsius%20on%20Wednesday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdelhi-temperature-now-just-4-4-degrees-shy-of-world-record-set-in-1913-5771883%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdelhi-temperature-now-just-4-4-degrees-shy-of-world-record-set-in-1913-5771883%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fdelhi-temperature-now-just-4-4-degrees-shy-of-world-record-set-in-1913-5771883%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%228%20Techies%20Who%20Switched%20Careers%20to%20Organic%20Farming%20%26amp%3B%20Found%20Ways%20to%20Make%20Profits%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EA%20pleasantly%20surprising%20trend%20is%20taking%20root%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20fields.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImagine%20switching%20the%20familiar%20click-clack%20of%20a%20keyboard%20for%20the%20earthy%20thud%20of%20a%20shovel%20and%20a%20hoe.%20A%20growing%20number%20of%20individuals%2C%20especially%20techies%2C%20are%20making%20this%20switch%20and%20embracing%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22n