20a%20year%20in%20people%20younger%20than%2055%2C%20according%20to%20existing%20research%20by%20The%20American%20Cancer%20Society.%20Although%20cases%20rose%20in%20all%20age%20groups%20under%2050%20during%20this%20period%2C%20the%20biggest%20uptick%20was%20seen%20in%20people%20in%20their%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-cases-doubled-young-people-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20late%2020s%20to%20early%2030s%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20rate%20of%20colon%20cancer%20for%20people%20in%20that%20age%20group%20increased%20by%20about%2070%25%20from%201999%20to%202020%2C%20according%20to%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20symptoms%2C%20such%20as%20weight%20loss%20and%20appetite%20changes%2C%20can%20be%20indicative%20of%20many%20illnesses%2C%20the%20authors%20of%20the%20news%20study%20published%20May%2024%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjamanetwork.com%2Fjournals%2Fjamanetworkopen%2Ffullarticle%2F2819248%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJAMA%20Network%3C%2Fa%3E%20wrote.%20This%20means%20they're%20often%20missed%2C%20leading%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fignored-colon-cancer-symptoms-diagnosis-abdominal-pain-bloody-stool-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elate-stage%20diagnosis%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20harder%20to%20treat%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20combat%20this%2C%20researchers%20used%20data%20from%2081%20studies%20across%20six%20countries%20involving%20nearly%2025%20million%20people%20under%2050%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-red-flag-signs-symptoms-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eearly-onset%20colon%20cancer%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Their%20aim%20was%20to%20determine%20which%20symptoms%20were%20most%20common%2C%20which%20signs%20put%20patients%20most%20at%20risk%20of%20colon%20cancer%2C%20and%20how%20long%20it%20took%20patients%20to%20get%20a%20colon%20cancer%20diagnosis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%2017%20signs%20of%20early-onset%20colon%20cancer%20were%20identified.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F3hOEB%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22The%2017%20signs%20of%20early-onset%20colon%20cancer%20identified%20in%20the%20study%5Cn%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22758%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20half%20of%20the%20participants%20had%20rectal%20bleeding%2C%20which%20was%20linked%20to%20a%20five-fold%20increase%20in%20early%20onset%20colon%20cancer%20risk%2C%20making%20it%20the%20largest%20risk%20factor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%2040%25%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F3-women-whose-abdominal-pain-and-other-symptoms-were-dismissed-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eabdominal%20pain%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20second%20most%20common%20symptom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChanges%20in%20bowel%20movements%20was%20the%20third%2C%20and%20included%20constipation%2C%20diarrhea%2C%20alternating%20bowel%20habits%2C%20or%20alternating%20diarrhea%20or%20constipation.%20The%20fourth%20most%20common%20symptom%20in%20the%20US%20was%20diarrhea%2C%20but%20in%20studies%20from%20non-US%20countries%2C%20it%20was%20loss%20of%20appetite%2C%20the%20study%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPatients%20tended%20to%20receive%20a%20cancer%20diagnosis%20between%20four%20to%20six%20months%20after%20their%20symptoms%20first%20appeared.%20It's%20not%20clear%20whether%20decreasing%20the%20time%20to%20diagnosis%20would%20improve%20outcomes%2C%20but%20the%20risk%20of%20cancer%20becoming%20advanced%20increases%20over%20time%2C%20the%20study%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20authors%20suggested%20that%20given%20the%20prevalence%20of%20rectal%20bleeding%20and%20abdominal%20pain%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fget-colonoscopy-colon-cancer-symptoms-colorectal-oncologist-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecolon%20cancer%20patients%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20doctors%20should%20always%20consider%20it%20before%20dismissing%20a%20patient%20with%20these%20symptoms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20significant%20differences%20in%20the%20studies%20used%2C%20which%20posed%20some%20challenges%20for%20analysis%2C%20the%20authors%20said.%20They%20were%20unable%20to%20compare%20colon%20cancer%20risk%20against%20other%20potential%20causes%20of%20symptoms%2C%20which%20might%20have%20provided%20a%20better%20picture%20of%20the%20relative%20risk%2C%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20still%20don't%20know%20what's%20behind%20the%20rise%20in%20colon%20cancer%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fultra-processed-foods-health-problems-study-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eultra-processed%20foods%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20environmental%20contaminants%2C%20and%20obesity%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20are%20being%20considered%20possible%20causes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Michael%20Shusterman%2C%20a%20gastrointestinal%20medical%20oncologist%20at%20NYU%20Langone's%20Perlmutter%20Cancer%20Center%20on%20Long%20Island%2C%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20to%20reduce%20the%20risk%20of%20developing%20colon%20cancer%2C%20he%20recommends%20patients%20quit%20smoking%3B%20cut%20down%20on%20alcohol%3B%20do%20some%20moderate-intensity%20exercise%3B%20eat%20more%20fiber%20and%20less%20red%20meat%3B%20and%20avoid%20ultra-processed%20foods%20as%20much%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-common-symptoms-colon-cancer-under-50s-chart-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716980132000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6655e168239fda2da6cbfb4e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmost-